The paper deals with clustering uncertain data, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of data management and mining. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to clustering based on a new notion of cluster centroid, which involves probabilistic modeling and statistical analysis. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
